    "Another crucial Mpox control method is vaccination.",
    "In certain epidemics, the smallpox vaccine, which guards against Mpox, has proven effective.",
    "Additionally, the CDC advises getting the JYNNEOS, ACAM 2000, or LC16m8 vaccine if they are 18 years old or older and at risk of direct exposure to Mpox.",
    "Antivirals for smallpox, such as tecovirimat and brincidofovir, have been made available by the Strategic National Stockpile because they may be useful in treating Mpox (Poland et al., 2022).",
    "Public health organizations should inform the public about the illness, how it spreads, and how crucial it is to get medical help right once if they think they may have come into contact with the virus."
